import React from 'react' import './AdminDisplay.css' import { useState } from 'react' export default function AdminDisplay() { const foodItems = [ { name: 'Item 1', mfg_exp: '12/2023', location: 'Pantry 1' }, { name: 'Item 2', mfg_exp: '01/2024', location: 'Pantry 2' }, { name: 'Item 3', mfg_exp: '06/2024', location: 'Pantry 3' }, { name: 'Item 4', mfg_exp: '07/2024', location: 'Pantry 4' }, { name: 'Item 5', mfg_exp: '12/2024', location: 'Pantry 5' }, { name: 'Item 6', mfg_exp: '03/2024', location: 'Pantry 6' }, { name: 'Item 7', mfg_exp: '01/2024', location: 'Pantry 7' }, ]; const[decline,setdecline] = useState(foodItems); const declinesetter = (itemIndex)=>{ const updatedItems = [...decline]; updatedItems.splice(itemIndex, 1); setdecline(updatedItems); } return (

Active Calories
